emotional%20nightmare%20at%20first%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20kids%20weren't%20happy%20about%20the%20move.%20The%20eldest%20literally%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BYou're%20ruining%20my%20life.%26quot%3B%20There%20was%20no%20turning%20back%2C%20though.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPreparing%20for%20the%20move%20meant%20we%20were%20completely%20swamped%20with%20the%20logistics%20of%20estate%20agents%2C%20removal%20companies%2C%20Facebook%20Marketplace%20postings%2C%20and%20video%20calls%20with%20schools%20in%20Buenos%20Aires.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20amount%20of%20things%20we%20collected%20as%20years%20went%20by%20was%20insane%2C%20and%20because%20the%20house%20was%20big%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdecluttering-cleaning-tips-home-closet-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewe%20kept%20them%20all%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20strollers%2C%20teddies%2C%20high%20chairs%2C%20rocking%20chairs%2C%20bottles%2C%20breast%20pumps%2C%20bicycles%2C%20scooters%2C%20puzzles%2C%20keyboards%2C%20microphones%2C%20blankets%2C%20books%2C%20you%20name%20it.%20Not%20to%20mention%20the%20piano%20and%20every%20single%20piece%20of%20furniture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20drove%20back%20and%20forth%20from%20the%20garbage%20dump%20so%20many%20times%2C%20and%20each%20time%20he%20came%20back%2C%20his%20face%20spoke%20to%20me%3A%20I'm%20exhausted%2C%20this%20is%20hard.%20We%20gave%20things%20away%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20the%20tears%20every%20time%20I%20put%20baby%20clothes%20in%20a%20bin%20bag%20and%20every%20time%20I%20dropped%20something%20meaningful%20at%20a%20charity%20shop.%20What%20am%20I%20doing%3F%20Am%20I%20crazy%3F%20I%20remember%20those%20thoughts%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20doubt%20and%20hardship%2C%20we%20kept%20going.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22297427c0-39fa-49f5-a45e-24dc6bcc919e%5C%22%3EWe've%20been%20in%20Argentina%20for%209%20months%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228660%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Colorful%20buildings%20with%20people%20w