ary%20that%20included%20over%202%2C400%20American%20adults%20found%20that%2070%25%20of%20parents%20expected%20to%20leave%20an%20inheritance%20to%20their%20children%20when%20they%20die.%20Of%20that%20group%2C%2076%25%20indicated%20they'd%20be%20open%20to%20considering%20passing%20down%20that%20inheritance%20early.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EDespite%20the%20interest%20in%20passing%20on%20wealth%20prior%20to%20their%20death%2C%20only%208%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20had%20actually%20done%20it.%20Meanwhile%2C%20only%204%25%20of%20adults%20said%20they%20had%20asked%20their%20parents%20for%20early%20inheritance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinancial%20planner%20Stoy%20Hall%20told%20BI%20many%20Americans%20who%20would%20like%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-inheritance-can-destroy-family-be-gift-estate-planning-attorney-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epass%20on%20wealth%3C%2Fa%3E%20just%20aren't%20sure%20if%20they%20can%20actually%20afford%20to%20do%20it.%20They're%20trying%20to%20make%20sure%20they%20have%20enough%20to%20live%20on%20without%20knowing%20what%20their%20future%20costs%20might%20be%2C%20while%20also%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20they%20can%20pass%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompounding%20the%20problem%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe%20don't%20talk%20about%20money%20enough%20in%20America.%26quot%3B%20Because%20talking%20about%20money%20is%20so%20taboo%2C%20he%20said%20parents%20and%20their%20adult%20children%20struggle%20to%20understand%20how%20the%20other%20is%20doing%20financially%20and%20what%20their%20needs%20look%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20kids%20don't%20know%20how%20much%20their%20parents%20do%20have%20or%20don't%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Bmakes%20it%20harder.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarding%20said%20part%20of%20the%20reason%20baby%20boomers%20are%20hesitant%20to%20part%20with%20their%20wealth%20is%20that%20for%20much%20of%20the%20generation%