0it%20again.%20It%20was%20also%20challenging%20being%20older%20than%20everyone%20around%20me%20and%20giving%20up%20a%20career%20that%20I%20was%20doing%20well%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20knew%20that%20this%20was%20my%20choice.%20I%20had%20already%20seen%20a%20different%20industry%2C%20and%20it%20just%20gave%20me%20further%20motivation%20to%20keep%20going%20and%20see%20myself%20grow.%20I%20ended%20up%20becoming%20a%20mentor%20to%20many%20of%20my%20classmates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20that%20my%20gift%20is%20to%20bring%20people%20together.%20I'm%20really%20good%20at%20working%20in%20teams%2C%20and%20little%20did%20I%20know%20that%20is%20what%20makes%20great%20engineers.%20I%20interviewed%20with%20and%20later%20joined%20Northrop%20Grumman%2C%20an%20aerospace%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b1ba5dec-a9bb-4a09-87e8-49eaf0275478%5C%22%3EI%20had%20impostor%20syndrome%20at%20my%20first%20job.%20Then%2C%20I%20worked%20on%20NASA's%20James%20Webb%20Space%20Telescope%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Karen%20Abarca%20of%20Northrop%20Grumman%20working%20on%20NASA's%20James%20Webb%20Space%20Telescope.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6866a5123d5881a51c1ca7da%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKaren%20Abarca%20began%20working%20at%20Northrop%20Grumman%20in%202020.%3Cp%3ENorthrop%20Grumman%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20definitely%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20impostor%20syndrome%20when%20I%20started%20at%20Northrop%20Grumman%20in%202020.%20I%20remember%20getting%20hired%20thinking%2C%20%26quot%3BThey're%20going%20to%20know%20that%20I%20don't%20know.%26quot%3B%20I%20just%20felt%20overwhelmed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20worked%20with%20a%20small%20team%2C%20but%20it%20was%20only%20a%20four-month%20project%2C%20so%20after%20that%2C%20my%20manager%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWhere%20do%20we%20put%20you%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3